---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navbar from "../components/Navbar.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Trust & Security — Datanika"
  description="Datanika's security architecture, compliance posture, data protection practices, and infrastructure overview. 109 security tests, SOC 2 Type I in progress."
>
  <Navbar />
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-20">
    <h1 class="mb-2 text-4xl font-bold gradient-text">Trust & Security</h1>
    <p class="mb-10 text-lg text-slate-400">
      How we protect your data, your credentials, and your pipelines.
    </p>

    <div class="space-y-12 text-slate-300 leading-relaxed [&_h2]:text-2xl [&_h2]:font-semibold [&_h2]:text-white [&_h2]:mb-4 [&_h3]:text-lg [&_h3]:font-medium [&_h3]:text-white [&_h3]:mb-2 [&_ul]:list-disc [&_ul]:pl-6 [&_ul]:space-y-2">

      <!-- Security Architecture -->
      <section>
        <h2>Security Architecture</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          Security is built into every layer of Datanika — from how we store credentials
          to how we isolate tenants. Our codebase is open-source, so every security claim
          below is verifiable in code.
        </p>

        <div class="grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/50 p-5">
            <h3>Multi-tenant isolation</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">
              All tables use <code class="text-violet-400">org_id</code> column filtering
              via <code class="text-violet-400">TenantMixin</code>. Every query is scoped
              to the authenticated organization. A dedicated
              <strong class="text-slate-300">cross-tenant isolation suite</strong> verifies
              that Org A cannot read, update, or delete Org B's data across connections,
              uploads, runs, and notifications, with additional
              <code class="text-violet-400">wrong_org</code> coverage in every service
              test module.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/50 p-5">
            <h3>Credential encryption</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">
              Connection credentials (API keys, database passwords, service account JSON)
              are encrypted at rest using <strong class="text-slate-300">Fernet</strong>
              symmetric encryption. Credentials are decrypted only at pipeline runtime,
              never logged, and never exposed in the UI after initial save.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/50 p-5">
            <h3>Authentication</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">
              Passwords are hashed with <strong class="text-slate-300">bcrypt</strong>.
              Sessions use <strong class="text-slate-300">JWT</strong> tokens. API access
              uses scoped API keys. SSO is available via <strong class="text-slate-300">SAML 2.0</strong>
              and <strong class="text-slate-300">OIDC</strong> on the Enterprise plan.
              OAuth login with Google and GitHub is available on all plans.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/50 p-5">
            <h3>Authorization</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">
              Role-based access control with four roles: <strong class="text-slate-300">Owner</strong>,
              <strong class="text-slate-300">Admin</strong>,
              <strong class="text-slate-300">Editor</strong>, and
              <strong class="text-slate-300">Viewer</strong>. Permissions are enforced at
              both the UI state layer and the service layer — no client-side-only guards.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/50 p-5">
            <h3>Audit logging</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">
              All mutations (create, update, delete) are logged with user ID, organization,
              action type, and timestamp. Audit logs are queryable per-org and retained
              for the lifetime of the account.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/50 p-5">
            <h3>Security testing</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">
              <strong class="text-slate-300">109 security test functions</strong> across
              10 dedicated test files covering authentication, injection, path traversal,
              tenant isolation, rate limiting, token security, file-upload security, CSRF,
              input validation, and API-key security. Every push to <code class="text-violet-400">dev</code>
              runs the full suite.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Compliance -->
      <section>
        <h2>Compliance</h2>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-violet-500/30 bg-violet-500/5 p-6 mb-6">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 mt-1">
              <svg class="h-6 w-6 text-violet-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m5.618-4.016A11.955 11.955 0 0112 2.944a11.955 11.955 0 01-8.618 3.04A12.02 12.02 0 003 9c0 5.591 3.824 10.29 9 11.622 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.042-.133-2.052-.382-3.016z" />
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-1">SOC 2 Type I — in progress</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">
                We are actively working toward SOC 2 Type I certification with a target
                completion in <strong class="text-slate-300">Q3 2026</strong>. Our 90-day
                readiness roadmap covers the CC1–CC9 Common Criteria control objectives,
                with approximately <strong class="text-slate-300">65% of controls already
                implemented in code</strong> — based on a control-by-control mapping of
                the CC1–CC9 points of focus against our existing security tests, audit
                logging, and access-control layers. The remainder is policy documentation
                and operational runbooks, in progress. Our full gap analysis is available
                under NDA on request. Vendor evaluation (Drata, Vanta, Secureframe) is
                underway, and an independent auditor will be engaged in the first phase.
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm text-slate-400 mt-2">
                If you're evaluating Datanika for an enterprise deployment and need details
                on our compliance timeline, contact
                <a href="mailto:security@datanika.io" class="text-violet-400 hover:underline">security@datanika.io</a>.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-white">GDPR:</strong> data processed and stored in the EU
            (Hetzner, Germany). Data Processing Agreement (DPA) available on request —
            email <a href="mailto:info@datanika.io" class="text-violet-400 hover:underline">info@datanika.io</a>.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-white">Data residency:</strong> all customer data resides
            in Hetzner's Falkenstein data center (Germany, EU). No data is transferred
            outside the EU unless explicitly configured by the customer (e.g., a BigQuery
            destination in US-region).
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-white">Data retention and deletion:</strong> pipeline run
            logs and metadata are retained for the lifetime of the account. Organizations
            and connections use a soft-delete model — records are marked deleted and
            removed from all application code paths, but the underlying
            Fernet-encrypted data remains in the database until a hard delete is triggered.
            Customers can request hard deletion of an organization and all associated
            data by emailing
            <a href="mailto:security@datanika.io" class="text-violet-400 hover:underline">security@datanika.io</a>.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Infrastructure -->
      <section>
        <h2>Infrastructure</h2>

        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-slate-800">
                <th class="text-left py-3 pr-4 text-slate-400 font-medium">Layer</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 pr-4 text-slate-400 font-medium">Provider</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 text-slate-400 font-medium">Details</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="text-slate-300">
              <tr class="border-b border-slate-800/50">
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-white">Application hosting</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4">Hetzner</td>
                <td class="py-3">Dedicated server, Falkenstein (Germany, EU). Ubuntu 24.04 LTS.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-slate-800/50">
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-white">CDN & DDoS protection</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4">Cloudflare</td>
                <td class="py-3">All traffic proxied. WAF rules, rate limiting, bot management.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-slate-800/50">
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-white">TLS</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4">Cloudflare + Nginx</td>
                <td class="py-3">TLS 1.2+ enforced. Cloudflare Origin Certificate for backend. HSTS enabled.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-slate-800/50">
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-white">Database</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4">PostgreSQL 16</td>
                <td class="py-3">Encrypted connections. Automated backups.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-slate-800/50">
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-white">Monitoring</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4">Prometheus + Grafana</td>
                <td class="py-3">Container metrics, resource utilization, alerting.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-white">Analytics</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4">Plausible CE</td>
                <td class="py-3">Self-hosted, cookie-free, GDPR-compliant. No third-party tracking.</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Subprocessors -->
      <section>
        <h2>Subprocessors</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          The following third-party services process data on behalf of Datanika customers:
        </p>

        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-slate-800">
                <th class="text-left py-3 pr-4 text-slate-400 font-medium">Subprocessor</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 pr-4 text-slate-400 font-medium">Purpose</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 text-slate-400 font-medium">Data location</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="text-slate-300">
              <tr class="border-b border-slate-800/50">
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-white">Hetzner Online GmbH</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4">Application hosting, database, worker processes</td>
                <td class="py-3">Germany, EU</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-slate-800/50">
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-white">Cloudflare, Inc.</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4">CDN, DDoS protection, DNS, TLS termination</td>
                <td class="py-3">Global (nearest PoP)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-slate-800/50">
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-white">Paddle.com Market Ltd</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4">Payment processing (Merchant of Record)</td>
                <td class="py-3">UK / EU</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-slate-800/50">
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-white">Google Workspace</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4">Business email (transactional emails via SMTP)</td>
                <td class="py-3">EU data region</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-white">GitHub (Microsoft)</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4">Source code hosting, CI/CD</td>
                <td class="py-3">US</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-slate-500">
          We notify customers of subprocessor changes at least 30 days in advance.
          To receive notifications, email
          <a href="mailto:info@datanika.io" class="text-violet-400 hover:underline">info@datanika.io</a>
          with subject "Subprocessor updates."
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Open Source -->
      <section>
        <h2>Open Source</h2>
        <p>
          Datanika's core is open-source at
          <a href="https://github.com/datanika-io/datanika-core" class="text-violet-400 hover:underline">github.com/datanika-io/datanika-core</a>.
          This means:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-white">Auditability:</strong> every security claim on this page
            is verifiable in the source code. The 109 security tests, the
            <code class="text-violet-400">TenantMixin</code>, the Fernet encryption layer —
            all public.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-white">No vendor lock-in:</strong> you can self-host Datanika
            on your own infrastructure with full control over data residency and network
            access. See the <a href="/docs/self-hosting" class="text-violet-400 hover:underline">self-hosting guide</a>.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-white">Community review:</strong> security-critical code paths
            benefit from community scrutiny in addition to our internal testing.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Responsible Disclosure -->
      <section>
        <h2>Responsible Disclosure</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          We take security vulnerabilities seriously. If you discover a vulnerability
          in Datanika, please report it responsibly:
        </p>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/50 p-6">
          <p class="text-white font-medium mb-3">Report a vulnerability</p>
          <p class="mb-3">
            Email
            <a href="mailto:security@datanika.io" class="text-violet-400 hover:underline font-medium">security@datanika.io</a>
            with a description, steps to reproduce, and affected components.
          </p>
          <div class="grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-3 text-sm">
            <div class="rounded border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900 p-3 text-center">
              <p class="text-slate-400">Acknowledgement</p>
              <p class="text-white font-semibold mt-1">48 hours</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900 p-3 text-center">
              <p class="text-slate-400">Initial assessment</p>
              <p class="text-white font-semibold mt-1">7 days</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900 p-3 text-center">
              <p class="text-slate-400">Patch release</p>
              <p class="text-white font-semibold mt-1">90 days</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-4">
            Full disclosure policy:
            <a href="https://github.com/datanika-io/datanika-core/blob/master/SECURITY.md" class="text-violet-400 hover:underline">SECURITY.md</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Contact -->
      <section>
        <h2>Questions?</h2>
        <p>
          For security questions, vulnerability reports, or DPA requests:
          <a href="mailto:security@datanika.io" class="text-violet-400 hover:underline">security@datanika.io</a>
        </p>
        <p class="mt-2">
          For general compliance inquiries and subprocessor update subscriptions:
          <a href="mailto:info@datanika.io" class="text-violet-400 hover:underline">info@datanika.io</a>
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
